								<div class="title" id="post-title-4420700">
																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nagiros" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4665703); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4665703&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203352" alt="Nagiros" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4665703)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nagiros" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4665703); return false;" >Nagiros</a></span> <span class="odate time_1573494867 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Nov 2019 17:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4420700">
									

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-size:90%;">Accompanying Music — <strong><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m27ZTza7DUc">Sing Me To Sleep</a></strong> by <strong><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnWfPDbkv0B9p1wPBUbODww">Matstubs</a></strong></span></p>
</div>
<p>This was a very personal tale to write, especially after a few months of forced hiatus. I hope you all like it. I've never done anything in this style before, and a big thank you goes to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kybard" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5717239); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5717239&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="Kybard" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5717239)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kybard" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5717239); return false;">Kybard</a></span> for refining it with a draft critique I desperately needed.</p>
<p>A companion piece (and refutation) may be in the works as well. Thanks for reading! ✨🦀✨</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Image&nbsp;Sources</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Image&nbsp;Sources</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Filename &quot;breaker&quot; was created by me from <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/local--files/main/250_logo.png">this asset</a>, with reference to <a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/f-o-u-r-t-e-e-n-thirteen/14-13-3.jpg">this art</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span> from <a href="/f-o-u-r-t-e-e-n-thirteen">F̶o̶u̶r̶t̶e̶e̶n̶ Thirteen</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fantem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1391641); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1391641&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="Fantem" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1391641)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fantem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1391641); return false;">Fantem</a></span>.</li>
<li>The Three Arrows pagebreak is public domain and sourced from <a href="https://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fitxer:Drei_Pfeile.svg">Wikipedia</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;A&nbsp;Note&nbsp;on&nbsp;References</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;A&nbsp;Note&nbsp;on&nbsp;References</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-size:75%;">Consider the following to be an incomplete list. I may have subconsciously drawn from other sources; for example, the &quot;moon no longer rose&quot; line may be a reference to &quot;Black Moon Howling&quot; or <a href="/shaggydredlocks-proposal">S. D. Locke's Proposal</a>, but I'm not sure.</span></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>The Foundation Over Heaven</p>
</blockquote>
<p>A reference to Heaven Ascension Dio's Stand from <em>JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Eyes of Heaven</em>, named <a href="https://jojo.fandom.com/wiki/The_World_Over_Heaven">The World Over Heaven</a>. The power of Dio's original Stand, The World, leads Dio to proclaim himself king over Earth and time. The World Over Heaven is its evolved form.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The serpent's eyes pierce through her darkened lair.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is Anantashesha, from <a href="/scp-3000">SCP-3000</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Their numbers flowed over plains and hills, led a shadowy colossus — the voice of The Administrator emanated from his lips.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The Administrator's design is evocative of my own <a href="/scp-4260">SCP-4260</a>, although he is not strictly SCP-4260 in this tale.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He was a man brought to the brink of the ultimate, striding unimpeded over mountains and trampling ancient land under the gravity of his personhood.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SRXYTh5Ri5g">Hmm.</a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Administrator's insignia shone bright against the crimson sky …</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Suggests the Scarlet King and apocalypse.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>like a policeman's badge: three inward arrows and a ring, branded onto moving flesh before his ascension.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Suggests the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Arrows">Three Arrows symbol</a>, although The Administrator's brand is the standard Foundation logo. I find it interesting that the two are so stylistically similar. When the Foundation logo was first suggested by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/far2" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172904); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172904&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="far2" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172904)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/far2" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172904); return false;">far2</a></span>, I recall is being likened to a police badge.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As gunfire engulfed the town, her fingerprint remained on the broken glass of that old window.</p>
<p>&#8230;</p>
<p>Giants were in motion between the corpses of skyscrapers, silently heralding a new Earth.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>References to memorable lines of <a href="/misery-makes-company">Misery Makes Company</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tiefling" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1474447); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1474447&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="Tiefling" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1474447)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tiefling" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1474447); return false;">Tiefling</a></span>. I really like that tale.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My body floats forever, the perfect anti-Talloran.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Alludes to <a href="/scp-3999">SCP-3999</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2527320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="LordStonefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2527320)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;">LordStonefish</a></span>, which I posit as SCP-3000's opposite.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Between cities and mountains walked everything ancient man had feared and hated. For a year, everything happened at once.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is inspired by the opening of <a href="/mud-on-the-carpet">Mud on the Carpet</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=388108&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="Djoric" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=388108)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;">Djoric</a></span>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Overhead, a mechanical giant loomed and wandered, glass eyes observing a glass world.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Suggests the Broken God from the <a href="/twistedgears-kaktus-proposal">TwistedGears-Kaktus Proposal</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;No, we can't ess-sea-pea that thing,&quot; said another.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Reference to how <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1593638337" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;">DrChandra</a></span>'s Herman Fuller characters talk about the Foundation, particularly in <a href="/scp-3717">SCP-3717</a>. It's only purpose here is to imply some sort of informational-breakdown.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Three inward shots rang out as I spiraled off the cliff edge.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Evokes the arrows from the Foundation logo.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>&quot;O World, O peoples, O Mankind: &#8230; May this foundation bring peace to Mankind.&quot;</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This language is very similar to the <a href="/doctors-of-the-church-hub">Doctors of the Church Hub</a>. All other connections are accidental.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Hear now our words of love to you, mere utterances from the dark.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>We die in the dark, and all that.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>traitors were shot behind the chemical shed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is a reference to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V_for_Vendetta">V for Vendetta</a>, which I hate. A character named Evey Hammond is tortured and threatened with execution &quot;behind the chemical shed&quot;. The graphic novel is noted for its praise of anarchist philosophy. Interestingly, no executions behind chemical sheds occur.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

